        <div class="col-lg-10">
            <div class="card p-4">
                <h1 class="text-center text-primary mb-4">Attendance Management System</h1>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Technology Stack</h4>
                    <p>ASP.NET, C#, HTML, CSS, Bootstrap, SQL Server</p>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Project Overview</h4>
                    <p>
                        I developed an Attendance Management System to automate the process of tracking, managing, and reporting employee attendance.
                        This system provides organizations with an efficient solution for maintaining accurate attendance records, improving operational transparency.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Key Highlights</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>User Interface:</strong> Designed a responsive and intuitive front-end using HTML, CSS, and Bootstrap.
                            The interface ensures easy navigation for administrators and employees across devices such as desktops, tablets, and smartphones.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Backend Development:</strong> Built with ASP.NET and C#, the system ensures modular, maintainable, and scalable code for managing attendance-related processes effectively.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Database:</strong> SQL Server was employed for secure and efficient data storage, managing attendance records, employee details, and leave information with robust CRUD operations.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Core Features</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Attendance Tracking:</strong> Automates daily attendance recording, supporting various input methods such as manual entry or integration with biometric systems.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Leave Management:</strong> Allows employees to apply for leaves and managers to approve or reject them. Tracks leave balances and integrates seamlessly with attendance records.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Real-Time Reporting:</strong> Generates real-time attendance reports for employees and departments, providing actionable insights for HR and management.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Monthly Summaries:</strong> Compiles monthly attendance data, including total workdays, leaves taken, and absenteeism, to aid in payroll processing.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Automated Alerts:</strong> Sends notifications for absenteeism trends, excessive leaves, or missing attendance entries, enabling proactive management.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Security Measures</h4>
                    <ul class="list-group">
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Role-Based Access Control:</strong> Implements secure authentication and authorization to restrict sensitive data access based on user roles (e.g., admin, employee).
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Data Validation:</strong> Ensures robust input validation on both client and server sides to prevent vulnerabilities like SQL injection and data breaches.
                        </li>
                        <li class="list-group-item">
                            <strong>Audit Trails:</strong> Maintains logs of system activities, including data changes and access attempts, for enhanced accountability and transparency.
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div class="mb-3">
                    <h4 class="section-title">Outcome</h4>
                    <p>
                        The Attendance Management System significantly improved the efficiency of tracking and managing employee attendance.
                        By automating attendance processes, the system reduced manual errors and provided valuable insights for better workforce management.
                        Its scalable architecture and secure design ensure that it meets the evolving needs of organizations, regardless of size.
                        This project demonstrates my proficiency in ASP.NET, C#, SQL Server, and front-end technologies, reflecting my ability to develop practical and secure enterprise solutions.
                    </p>
